  "text": "where n df is the number of deformations of the string web, n X is the number of external legs, F int in the number of internal faces, and F is the total number of faces. In case there are \"hidden\" faces, F should be replaced by the total number of points in the respective grid diagram [CITATION_1] . After lifting to M theory we find the highest spin for a massive membrane multiplet ending on a 5-brane and breaking 8 supercharges",
